  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-01-01",
  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "A population is the complete set of individuals, items, or observations that a statistical study aims to describe. It is the thing you actually want to know about — the sample is just the means by which you learn. If a medical researcher wants to know whether a drug lowers blood pressure in adults, the population is all adults (or perhaps all adults with hypertension, depending on the research question). If a manufacturer wants to know the defect rate of its products, the population is every item produced.\n",
